This repository contains a distributed messaging and synchronization protocol in c/c++.

The ultimate goal is to implement a simple distributed messaging and synchronization
protocol that can be integrated with Application and free the application from deading
with networking, messaging format, synchronization of concurrent read & write of the
same dataset with support of conflict detection and resolution in multiple levels of
the protocol.

The library is implemeneted in C++ and hopefully it is doing it right way through
delegation design pattern and fully extensible and customizable without proliferation
of Classes.

Note about building within Dockerfile container:
0. build container - "docker build -t dmn ."
1. run container (interactive mode) - "docker run -it --rm dmn"
2. remove built container - "docker rmi dmn"

Kafka network setup:
0. docker build -t dmn-kafka -f DockerfileKafka .
1. docker network create dmn-kafka-net
2. docker run -d --name kafka-server --network dmn-kafka-net dmn-kafka
3. docker run -it --network dmn-kafka-net dmn-kafka bash
   - ./bin/kafka-topics.sh --create --topic timer_counter --bootstrap-server kafka-server:9092
   - ./bin/kafka-console-producer.sh --topic timer_counter --bootstrap-server kafka-server:9092
4. docker run -it --network dmn-kafka-net dmn-kafka bash
   - ./bin/kafka-console-consumer.sh --topic timer_counter --bootstrap-server kafka-server:9092
